text: A by-election was held for the New South Wales Legislative Assembly electorate of Auburn on 9 November 1946 following the resignation of Jack Lang who had resigned to successfully contest the seat of Reid at the 1946 Australian federal election. His son, James Lang, won the by-election for his father's old seat. ==Results== ==References== Category:1946 elections in Australia Category:New South Wales state by-elections Category:1940s in New South Wales Category:November 1946 events
title: 1946 Auburn state by-election
